name: Dr. Kirti Chopra
about: Dr. Chopra, a top graduate of Indiana University School of Dentistry and a member of Omicron Kappa Upsilon, is a restorative cosmetic dentist committed to excellence. With over 500 hours of continuing education, she specializes in Invisalign, Cosmetic Dentistry, Bioclear, Digital Dentistry, and Full Mouth Rehabilitation. A Kois Center graduate, she is also pursuing accreditation with the AACD. Beyond dentistry, she finds inspiration in her family, bringing joy and dedication to her work.

questionResponses.response: To experience dentistry redefined. We are dedicated to enhancing your smile's natural beauty and improving your oral health.

question.question: Why should patients choose you as their provider instead of others in the area
question.example: I've been practicing dentistry for over 17 years, and treat a wide range of issues. Our practices focuses on making sure that you are 100% involved in your healthcare choices, and that you always feel safe and comfortable. Our practice also offers a wide range of payment options to match your needs.

questionResponses.response: Invisalign, smile makeovers, and Dental emergencies

question.question: What are the top 3 treatments that you focus on
question.example: I am skilled in all areas of dentistry, but primarily focus on Cosmetics, Invisalign, Oral Surgery and Teeth Whitening in my practice. I believe very strongly in continuing my education and completing advanced training programs in Orthodontics, Periodontics, Endodontics and Cosmetic Dentistry to make sure I can provide the highest quality of dentistry to all my patients.

questionResponses.response: We are home to Advanced, Responsible, and Comprehensive Dentistry. We follow evidence-based dentistry and continually improve our skills and knowledge, so we can offer you modern dentistry

question.question: What are you proud of in your practice
question.example: Something that makes me very proud is that our practice has good reviews because of our experienced staff, attractive aesthetics and advanced equipment. It's fully accessible and designed for geriatric care and patients with mobility issues.

questionResponses.response: We offer various services to improve the aesthetic appearance of patients' smiles. This includes teeth whitening, veneers, crowns, Invisalign, dental bonding, and smile makeovers

question.question: Which cases do you enjoy treating? Why
question.example: I truly enjoy treating all my patients. However, one of the most rewarding moments for a dentist is to see a patient leave the office with a beautiful smile on their face while only a short time ago they were experiencing discomfort, pain or embarrassment to smile.
